http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Stage-being-set-for-fete/article13983735.ece

Preparing the stage for the 56{+t}{+h}State School Arts Festival to be held in the city later this month, the kaal naattu karmam (placing of the central pole) was held at Putharikandam Maidan, the main venue of the festival, on Tuesday.Inaugurating the ceremony, Education Minister P.K. Abdu Rabb said that all the venues would be readied for the event in a time-bound manner. No efforts would be spared in constructing the main venue in the best-possible manner. “The fete was previously held in Thiruvananthapuram in 2010, which was the final year in the tenure of the previous Left Democratic Front (LDF). Incidentally, the upcoming event is also being organised as the term of the current government is nearing its end. All attempts should be made to uphold the high standards set by the previous editions of the festival,” Mr. Rabb said.Health Minister V.S. Sivakumar who presided over the function called for ensuring coordination among the officials concerned and members of the organising committees for the smooth conduct of the event. Director of Public Instruction M.S. Jaya welcomed the gathering. Additional Director of Public Instruction Johns V. John and Vocational Higher Secondary Education (VHSE) Director K.P. Noufal were among those who were present on the occasion.A ‘pandal’ that can accommodate nearly 5,000 persons is being set up at the main venue. The facility will have separate enclaves for green rooms, rest rooms, VIP section and others.On Wednesday afternoon, Mr. Rabb will preside over a meeting to assess the work of the various subcommittees at the festival welcome committee office at Government Model Boys Higher Secondary School, Thycaud.